This is the Perl module YAML::Active.

INSTALLATION

YAML::Active installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is set up, you
should just be able to do

    % cpan YAML::Active

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

YAML::Active documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc YAML::Active

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

